-- Tom Tailor says consortium headed by Fosun to buy 23 pct stake
-- 
-- Wed Jul 30, 2014 01:20PM EDT
-- None



FRANKFURT, July 30 (Reuters) - Tom Tailor <TTIGn.DE> on Wednesday said a consortium controlled by China's Fosun International Ltd has agreed to buy a 23.16 percent stake in the German retailer currently owned by Liechtenstein-based Versorgungs- und Förderungsstiftung.

Tom Tailor said the acquisition of the stake by Fidelidade-Companhia de Seguros SA, Portugal, an insurance company controlled by Fosun, will be implemented shortly. The Fosun consortium also includes other co-investors and some members of the retailer's management board, Tom Tailor said.